result.execSummary:
The defendant Shawn M. Hammond was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess GHB,GB,BDO, Ketamine, Flunitraz., a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(f).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:36 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Shawn M. Hammond in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Theresa A Beck appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent.  
Mr. Hammond waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
State files information; Arraignment:--service of Information admitted, reading waived--maximum penalties recited

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds the Defendant  guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Hammond to 3.5 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 18 months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 2 years, consecutive. This sentence is IMPOSED & STAYED and the Court places the Defendant on Probation for 3 years with conditions:
--Comply with all of the Chapter 51 orders and conditions
--AODA Assessment, Counseling & Follow-through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other type of assessment, treatment or counseling as per Agent
--Random drug/alcohol screening
--Make honest & legitimate efforts to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--No possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--No Contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate per Agent

If revoked, The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and the Substance Abuse Program. 
If revoked, The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served.

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant
